Scope declared by braces. Can be global or local to function
or loop. 

Local scope overrides all inherited scope.

int tune = 20;

int main() {
	int tuna = 3;
	cout << tuna << endl; //returns 3
}

How to use global variable: unary scope operator

:: - unary scope operator

int main() {
	int tuna =3 ;
	cout << ::tuna << endl; //returns 20
} 

:: - is for global variables of current program
